article.headline: Winthrop 98, Northern Illinois 97 (2OT)
article.story: ROCK HILL, S.C. (AP) -- James Shuler's 3-pointer with 3.1 seconds left in double-overtime helped Winthrop beat Northern Illinois 98-97 on Saturday, The Huskies (13-10) had a chance to tie or win after Cory Sims was fouled at the buzzer trying a desperation 3. But he only hit one of his three foul shots. Shuler, who finished with a career-best 27 points, helped the Eagles (18-6) come back from a 12-point second half deficit. Shuler hit two free throws to tie it at 77 with 23 seconds left in regulation. Shuler's 3-pointer with 1:45 to go in the first overtime tied the game at 85. Neither team would score the rest of the period. In the second overtime, Todd Peterson's back-to-back 3-pointers put Northern Illinois ahead 93-91. But the Huskies hit only four of their seven free throws in the final minute. Craig Bradshaw scored a career-best 24 points and Torrell Martin added 20 points for the Eagles, who will travel to Northern Illinois next year as part the Bracket Buster series that matched the two teams. Peterson led Northern Illinois with 21 points and nine rebounds, while Sims added 15 points and nine assists.
